    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Chinese Goal for 2008</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Mark Zidzik says China would surely fulfill its goal of having 2008 Olympics held in Beijing (Sept 6 article) if it evacuated Tibet and returned it to Tibetans</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For a Prize That's Olympian, China Jumps the Gun'' (Beijing Journal, Sept. 6):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For a Prize That's Olympian, China Jumps the Gun'' (Beijing Journal, Sept. 6):</p>
        <p>You report that in hopes of having Beijing selected as the host city for the 2008 summer Olympics, the Chinese are ''determined that no price is too high to land the Games this time, no flaw too small to expunge in order to succeed.''</p>
        <p>In the spirit of international cooperation, I respectfully suggest that China evacuate Tibet and return it to the Tibetans. Following my suggestion will practically guarantee China the fulfillment of its Olympian goal.</p>
        <p>MARK ZIDZIK  Plainsboro, N.J., Sept. 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
